{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CMWFZv1eJTVa2HJtVN3Yeq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It seems elasticsearch-2 can't connect to elasticsearch-0 (connect_exception on port 9300). This is the transport port. That's because elasticsearch-0 was recently restarted and may still be starting up.\n\nBut the issue is that all 3 pods are 0/1. Let me check what's happening with elasticsearch-0 specifically since it was the last to be restarted.\n\nActually, I think the issue is that the StatefulSet rolling restart restarted all nodes, and since they were all restarted in sequence, the cluster might have had a brief period where the quorum was lost. \n\nNow all three nodes are coming back online and attempting to reconnect. Looking at the startup probe configuration, there's a 30-second initial delay before checks begin, then 10-second intervals with a threshold of 30 failures, giving each pod up to 330 seconds total to become ready. Since the pods have only been running for 2-4 minutes, they should still be within that window. The real issue is why they're not becoming Ready yet—I should check what's actually happening inside elasticsearch-0 to see if the process is running correctly.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1395,"cache_read_input_tokens":48406,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1395},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0cd4ff8e-42d6-47ed-8f89-a407d46a89b3","uuid":"11f653ff-2823-4a0a-9e94-39f5fdd78b52","request_id":"req_011CcPAQ3K91EjSgmTgmgnZe"}
