{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01SFHxsKfzRVsbrqAUdtJ5wb","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a critical problem. After restarting elasticsearch-0, the password is back to the original `elasticpass`. Why?\n\nBecause the ES StatefulSet has:\n```yaml\n- name: ELASTIC_PASSWORD\n  valueFrom:\n    secretKeyRef:\n      key: password\n      name: elastic-password\n```\n\nThe `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env var is used by the Elasticsearch Docker image to SET the initial password when the cluster is bootstrapped. But in the running container, if the password has been changed via the API, the env var is not used to re-set it.\nWhen the pod restarts, Elasticsearch reads the `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` env var and the container's entrypoint script uses it to reset the password during startup. So when the pod restarted after I updated the secret, it reset the password back to `elasticpass` instead of keeping my API change.\n\nThe sequence was: I updated the secret to the new password, used the ES API to change it, but then the pod restarted and the entrypoint script reset it back to the secret value. Now I'm getting a 401 even with the new password, so let me check if the old password still works.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":594,"cache_read_input_tokens":49801,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":594},"output_tokens":24,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0cd4ff8e-42d6-47ed-8f89-a407d46a89b3","uuid":"bfab7e25-d047-4894-ad6e-00a4b40cf7eb","request_id":"req_011CcPAR4Lvx3h59C72Yg3Za"}
