{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01N58TbudWEBT3nStgXsHNXh","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The critical error is:\n```\n\"failed to retrieve password hash for reserved user [elastic]\"\n\"error.message\":\"at least one primary shard for the index [.security-7] is unavailable\"\n```\n\nThe `.security-7` index's primary shard is unavailable. This index stores security configuration including passwords. The cluster is up (we can see the cluster UUID) but the security index hasn't been properly initialized.\n\nThe problem is that since there are no PVCs, the cluster started fresh. In Elasticsearch 8.x, when a node starts fresh with `ELASTIC_PASSWORD` set, it sets the bootstrap password. \n\nBut here's the issue: the cluster UUID matches the old cluster, which suggests the same node IDs are being reused even though the data was lost. This means the pods are being restarted rather than replaced, so the container's writable layer is being preserved across restarts.\n\nActually, no—`kubectl rollout restart` does recreate the pods entirely, which means new containers are created and the data at `/usr/share/elasticsearch/data` should be lost. Yet the cluster UUID is still the same, which is puzzling because that UUID should be stored in the data directory. If the data were truly gone, the cluster should bootstrap fresh with a new UUID.\n\nThe real problem might be that the `.security-7` index has unassigned shards, which could be preventing the cluster from fully initializing. The cluster UUID persists in the data directory, so even with pod restarts, if the volumes are retained, the same UUID would appear. The real issue is that the `.security-7` index shards are unavailable—likely because the cluster is still forming and hasn't fully initialized the security index yet, even though it's responding to authentication requests.\n\nLet me look at how the StatefulSet volumes are configured to understand whether data is actually persisting across restarts.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":7820,"cache_read_input_tokens":52005,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":7820},"output_tokens":23,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"0cd4ff8e-42d6-47ed-8f89-a407d46a89b3","uuid":"79126446-99e5-42f1-9a51-d987fae0da8f","request_id":"req_011CcPATtpmeQreekHfdJMV9"}
